content: It's not worth it
Great app
Not enough options for a small family. If you have 1 toddler or 2 small kids, you get maybe 1-2 poses. Not worth the $2. I'll just Google poses instead.
I paid for glamour posed but it ain't activated
Doesn't work for Android 10

perfect app for posing on the go. I agree with the other review to add to extra more modern poses. Or the ability to create a folder for each event and also have must have shots especially for wedding photography.
I've been using this app for quite some time now and although I love the app and it's simplicity, I really wish they would add some new poses.
Crashes when I open my favorites
Great app for photography, would be even better if there was an option to save favourites in fokders, so favorite family poses, couples etc rather than in one list

I was looking online for poses for my first wedding shoot and many of the ones I liked best came from this website with these drawings. Decided to get the app to keep it all in one place even though many reviewers were disappointed about the price and or in-app purchases. The convenience, execution, and simplicity easily make this worth $4 total in my opinion. Thank you so much for this app it will relieve much of my event-day stress!!!
Good app for new photographer
Please,  allow to add custom notes and tags to poses, as well as link to sample photos taken at past shoots.
This is an excellent app with loads of good posing ideas that can be developed into many more. It also gives good advice on refining the pose. I would recommend this to any photographer.
Good app  even though the pricing is deceptive.
For a new photographer, it is a well made app that  give them a general idea on how to position the subject. For anyone else, it the app leaves you wanting more advanced tips and tricks on posing.
I paid for the app with the expectation that more poses would be added. They added them but if u want to see them you need to pay again... no thank you !! DELETED APP!!
How  about maternity and newborn poses?
App has saved me many times. The option to transfer to SD Card doesn't work, saying there is no space.
I find it to be really useful and helps with a lot of photos. I wish there was a pregnancy section but didn't have any luck finding anything that would fit. Also wish it had more for larger women.
I have had this app for several years and refer back to it often for ideas.
This is really convenient for Portrait shoots!
A very excellent app, has some very interesting poses.

I think the only additional thing I'd like to see with this app is the ability to flag or favourite a list of poses so that if I choose a set of poses, I can bring up just that list for my model or client and not have to scroll through the entire set.
Very easy to understand and very helpful to use on any photoshoot.
Not worth the money.

I paid for this app even though there were very few poses but there was the promise more were on their way.  The "update" finally arrived but the developer wants more money for what s/he implied was part of the original purchase. This is deceptive and dishonest and because of this I will never purchase anything from "MENDO STA" again.                  Loaded app again after waiting a few years to see if it improved, it hasn't. Still a ripoff.
Simple idea, well executed and reasonably priced.
Awesome stuff!

This has been an excellent app for creating a 'same page' moment between photographer (me) and models. It has easy instructions for getting the pose. I do hope more poses will be added. But even as is there are many poses included. This is a totally helpful and useful app. Worth more than is asked.
Really like it, adds more variety to photos and easy to understand
Perfect
Lots of good tips and poses.... Will come in handy
Simple and effective.
Working in a portrait studio this app helps me get a break from the boring corporate protocol and still take great shots! Definitely worth the few dollars!
I have been looking for the app since I read the tutorial o  DPS. I am happy I found it for minimal cost. I'd definitely recommend it to other photographers.
I liked it but it stopped working after I updated my phone. I sent an email with the error to the app developer and never got a response
The app is simple to use yet powerful. The poses are well set out.
I loved the App, no doubts bot it. But hvnt recived much updates since I bought it. Though I see some new poses are being added on website but updates are not released for the app.
Amazing app
Only needs high fashion model poses! Also would be nice to have a section to put our own ideas, just to have a catalogue of poses.

This looks good on my Nexus 7, But very aliased on my small 240x320 LG, which I'm planning to use on the field Can you optimize the downscaling, or include small size versions in case of smaller displays?
I've learned more about photography with this $2 app vs reading photography websites for 10 years.
Please update icon little smaller. It's looks very big in mobile compared to latest icons
Works great on-the-go. Has good ideas for posing and it's super helpful to jog your memory for posing when you're doing a photo shoot.

Are you kidding me? I bought this app in middle of shoot.  First it was free, not its paid and you added Glamor shots paid?  Not a good idea. I would give definitely 5 stars but you disappoint me. How about refunding for not showing Glamor shots in there? Be nice and include glamour shots in paid app next update.   We are professionals, not kids who do in app purchases.
Good apps. But Package invalid after upgraded to android 4.2.2. Please upgrade!
This is a good App, but extra pay for additional 86 poses!
Great app
Very well prepared app, great comments
Promised of updating poses the only update you have to pay for it
Looks ok... basic tips, but no mention that this is NOT the full app. You need to pay extra for the full app - don't understand that and wish I'd read other reviews before I'd purchased...
Easy to use and lots of great looking poses with useful  tips.

I've tried countless posing apps and even collected images on my own for posing examples.  The two biggest problems I've had is a convenient way to access the collection and the distraction caused by the actual subject, especially for boudoir type poses.   It was easy to be distracted by the subject in the image and loose sight of the pose itself.  This app solves both of those problems.   The line drawings are well done and the organization is easy to use.  The favorites feature is just awesome icing on the cake.  Well done.    If I have one feature wish, it would be that there's some mechanism to either add additional poses myself, or be able to submit them for consideration for future updates.
Great app, originally not compatible with Nexus 7. I see it now its. Thank you.
Been too long since updated, would like to see more posing option's for kids, families,  bridal party,  etc. Good poses and explanations but not entirely happy with only one update in over a year.
The app is very good and gives some sound advice and tips, but like many people have mentioned, you have to pay an additional charge for the glamour poses, which is a bit of a con...
I love this app's simplicity, variety of poses and ease of use.

The tips section offers some good sound advice and the poses are much better in line drawing like this than in other apps where they show the pose in a full photo which distracts from the posing subject..In short I like the way this app is built.
It helped me a lot while I was on an assignment.
I have to say that it does make you pay extra for the additional poses but I paid for it and I think it's definitely worth it this is going to help a lot

Poses will definitely help in future shoots. I've shown similar illustrations to subjects and they suddenly 'get it'... where words fail, pix help.  Could include more illustrations... hopefully this app will be expanded.

I don't know why people are moaning about the price for this. £3.28 for this inc the glamour addon. If you use this for a profession or even just to learn,  For what it could do for you or your career is priceless...
When will there be more updates with other poses
Covers the main basic position, for both sexes and different posing situations, but does not warrant the purchase price!
Awesome!

Ideal for any photographer, most likely ideal for any model too, the app while i thought slighty expensive at first is quite good value, but the glamour in app purchase add on is very cheeky and should be free, the developer should realise this and not be too greedy

Charging again using in-app purchasing for an update (glamour shots) after already buying the app is just plain wrong. I still disagree with the author's decision on that. The latest update does fix the technical issues though and the new poses added a lot of value. Raising from my previous 1 star to three. At least he tells you in the description about it now.  If he'd only sold the glamour poses as a separate app most of the bad reviews wouldn't have happened.

Come on man, fix the app! Im using the nexus 7 and like so many others the have complained, the text description that is accompanied with the pics are cut out, you cannot even resize the pic to display the text.  Fix this asap please! Edit: They have fixed the app for my nexus devices and have added more possess.  The possess themselves are easy to follow and set up. The descriptions are a bit short in some instances however. I was not charged again like some users indicated. I recommend this app over!
This helps me direct poses whenever I ran out of creative juice
Charging again after paying?
Simple but easy to use as show, should add a few more poses in the future
I bought a new phone. Android as the previous but now the app crashes at startup and I cant use it anymore...! Bs!
Pay for the extra glamour poses and restart the phone and can't install the extra poses again. Why I don't pay attention to previous reviews???

Great cheat sheet. The app now works as it should on my device. I can save my favorites without crashing and can now view the thumbnails properly. Developer responded quickly to my issues and now everything works. Yes, you can find almost all of these poses on DPS but it is nice to have it in an app where I can organize everything. Also, I don't mind the Glamour shots being an extra $2 I knew about it through reading the reviews though, not from the app description.
Very nice poses..  app works very smoothly on my galaxy s3
It's not working properly with my Samsung note 2. Pictures and menu going to almost 1mm every opening. I hate it... Developer didn't answer my emails about this problem. No one care you...
Very poor poses..
Useful app for photographers to help show what they want. Not overly impressed with paying for the additional poses. Not worth the additional cost.
I should of read reviews before purchase! You have to pay extra for glamour poses! Greedy company! Dont buy!
It kept hanging. Please fix. I already try re-install the app, it's not working.

Fairly good app, but two issues:  1. no landscape (horizontal) image formating. 2. Once selecting a pose, you have to enlarge the image to get to a full screen view.    As a photographer I don't want to be touching the phone so much to present a pose to my subject.  It needs to be a "fast-select" that I can show the subject.  And of course, I agree with others - shouldn't have to pay extra for the "glamour" poses.  These are drawings, not photos - not even close to adult content.

I have no clue what everybody else is talking about. Seriously. This app has asked for permission to access internet only. Which is pretty much the same as every OTHER app out there on the market.  I do wish it had more poses, but the ones here will work in such a huge variety of ways that I haven't actually ran out of poses to use and try. And I'm out shooting every day.  This app is easier than a posing guide with actual images. It's less intimidating, my clients (even those that aren't really young, or thin) can follow it easily and it's so simple to use that I prefer it over other posing guides that I've paid a whole lot more for.  I recommend this app to all of my friends, like all the time. It's a huge steal at only a few bucks. Huge.

This is a great app for photographers with or without experience.  I think its pretty pathetic that everyone is complaining about the extra fee for more poses.  This person took the time to compile these poses. And then took more time to add more. As photographers YOU all should know that time is valuable.  Kudos to the author for making more available, shame on everyone else for not valuing the time and effort to make this available.  </rant>

used this today and got some brilliant results! good to show the subjects and help them feel comfortable knowing how the pic could look. well worth buying.  5 stars. would pay extra for updates and extra poses in all categories.
I wish there was an update to resolve the display issue on Google Nexus 7. I can't see all texts. More poses please...

I liked the app when I purchased it, but making the new category of glamour poses the same cost as the app itself is ridiculous, imo. We paid for the app, the updates should include all new poses even those added in new categories. I'll just go bookmark the glamour poses included in Digital Photography School's recent blog post...FOR FREE!!!
Love the app, and when I need help I received fast and excellent support.  Great developer.
Good poses, but that extra cost for the only poses I was ever after is absolute garbage
Crashes when trying to mark a pose as favorite. Just line drawings so it is impossible to see lighting. Most poses are designed for young and thin models.
I need to pay more for last section. Not good!

As a hobby photographer, the application comes in very handy when my friends, or friends of friends ask me to shoot some personal portraits. I go over all the available poses and let them select the ones they feel comfortable with before the shoot and use the sketch on the app to help guide them into it while shooting, trying slight variations on each as well.

I'm with the consensus here, we literally have to buy the app again, to get updated poses, that were already promised! Nice job Kaspars Grinvalds but you forgot to mention the part about "and for an additional $1.99......" Yeah, its only two bucks but its the principle. You charge users with the "lite" app sure, but not users with the (eh-em) FULL app.
All sorts of display issues. The menu on the left while in portrait mode doesn't display images. Can't read image all description text. Works OK on phone. Needs more poses.
At first was ok they promised more poses. What they didn't mention was at an extra cost. Not worth it!
The poses are very limited, which are in fact are already available for free on internet. You will have to further purchase any new content added. Rip Off..

I purchased this app the first day it was out, poses were limited but purchased to encourage and in the hopes of new poses coming as updates. Yes, new poses came with updates but if you want them you have to pay extra.... NOT COOL!

its got what you need quick and to the point, my only suggestion woukd be to add some lighting  suggestions.   WELL AFTER REVIEWING THIS AND PROMISING ADDITIONAL POSES THE SELLER DECIDES TO NOT ONLY ASK FOR PERMISSIONS TO MY SYSTEM BUT WANTS TO CHARGE ME  THE ADDITIONAL POSES.   THUMBS DOWN
As others have mentioned you wll have to pay again to unlock new poses. Since update I can't open the app on my Samsung Galaxy S so it's useless.
This is a joke, when you have to pay for upgrade.

After buying app u find all the poses are emailed free through DPS. They promise new poses, none was forthcoming and when it did get released they demand in app purchase for already paying customers. Totally wrong. Do not buy this app as u will find the poses for free on DPS - thats digital photography school. Too greedy think.

Has great assortment of poses. And since they are drawings, you, or your client, don't get hung up on the models looks. Some Posing apps have the same basic pose over and over with different models, this is good clean info without the photographer that created the app going on an Ego trip.
Far too few poses for far too much. This should be free to entice new customers and keep previous ones happy. Very promising app that has failed to deliver.
App  freezes on my phone
1 star since you have to pay for updates! That is SO wrong and you will lose a lot of people because of it.

This is a nice little app for convenience, and like many others I purchased this in the hopes of more poses to be added to make it worth the initial price. These are just sketches, and it's not lile you added significantly more information. I think i'm just going to make a gallery of real pictures of poses on my phone, which will be better and free. Good luck charging so much for your little sketches.
Bought the app to support the developer. Will not buy an update at the cost of the app just for 56 new glamour poses. Probably won't buy any future updates either.
In attempting to make you spend more on this APP it holds your memory hostage.... SCAM
Jog on!
Why do we need to pay for the glamour? It should be free. Because of this I'm giving 1 star review only

I like the app. I purchased the app not long ago. The developer mentioned that more poses were coming soon. The new version is here and to get the new poses you must purchase them in app.  Developer please post how much the additional poses are going to cost. I have not upgraded my version to the latest version.  Please don't nickel and dime us. I will pay a reasonable price for good poses and an ample number of updates. Maybe separate into genres and charge separately for each style pack.
Seriously, charging FULL PRICE for UPDATES???? and the updates CRASH the phone. SO sorry I purchased this now.  I WANT A REFUND.

I don't mind paying a tiny bit to upgrade to the glamour poses.  Not everybody shoots nude and boudoir photos, so those who don't have no need to pay for the extra category.  I didn't know if Google Play would charge me twice when I accessed them on my phone after buying them on my tablet, since there was no extra app to download, but it didn't and gave me access when I hit the back button from the accept-charge page.  The poses are good.  I like another reviewer's idea of poses for large people, people with big noses, etc. and I'd also like to see poses for people in wheelchairs and people with other physical challenges.
Great app; comes in very handy!

I purchased this app and thought that there would be updates that would be free only to find out that us PAID app supporters have to pay for extra poses now too?  Why not have a free limited version and a paid full version?
I am really disappointed that the update is only available if you pay more for an app that I already paid for. Bad business.
Crap I already bought, expect updates to be free. Noone else does that when buying an app. Straight greed!
Adding new posers but having to pay for them, no thanks!

There should be a negative 'star' for something like this. I paid for the app to support the Dev, and this new update introduces a new pack of poses with a catch that you have to pay again. Really unfair

App WAS mediocre at best. Limited selection of poses. Purchased & gave 5 stars to encourage developer because I liked the idea and thought this app could someday be polished & great. Charging for more poses is a step in the wrong direction.
Shouldn't have to keep buying updates. Updates should have new free poses

I have to agree with another user on the matter of a new category being added. Don't buy the app. now, wait for 5 years then maybe all of the categories will be there so you don't have to keep purchasing.
Does one thing very well and is a great value for just $2.  Extra points for not requiring any permissions. Please add hardware acceleration for smoother scrolling on newer handsets

Don't appreciate being made to pay twice, I've only had this app a few days but it said that more poses were coming soon before I purchased (didn't mention about needing to pay extra)   Good app and will happily give it five stars if this joke is sorted. (by all means if you want to make more money then raise the price of the app but shouldn't expect customers to pay twice)   All the poses in this are available for free online (not sure about the new glamour ones but I'm sure they are)

I think this app is helpful and fantastic. The only thing they could add to make it 5-stars would be to have categories for faves and maybe tips for specific body types/issues (example pear shapes etc. )
"More poses coming soon..."  Didn't expect that future poses would require additional purchases.  Makes the app a little less desirable.  I probably would have raised the price for future app buyers.

PURCHASING THE APP DOES NOT UNLOCK ALL POSES. After buying the app, the developer requires you to pay to unlock poses. And it seems as though he'll continue to to charge for additional poses with every update.

In the description it promises new poses, however doesn't explain that you'll have to pay for them each time they release a new set. Already paid for the app, do the right thing and not charge us for something that is promised. Will change to 5 stars if fixed.
This is an excellent resource.
Full of concise, exceptionally useful tips. Enthusiastically recommended!
This is the application for newbies in photography, the images are great, the app works fine in my tablet. The only i need, more posing images :D and more tips.
I like it
This a great app to get you going into any shoot! Quick review beforehand gets your head in the game!
good app
I really Like this App.
This app is perfect for serious photographers . I say this is worth buy.
Good ideas in an easy to navigate format. How abt some baby posing idea's? This app still deserves 5 stars tho! SE neo v
finally a quick and easy posing app that works and i can use!! thanks
Not ton of content but the content is quality. Worth the price.
This is the ideal app for poses! It's easy, categorized well, and the drawings are easier to see than an actual picture. Absolutely love it! It would be nice to see a category for family portraits.
A great app finally support GSM Galaxy Nexus!
Sketches are great.
Cant for an update, great to have when you draw a blank.  Would love tips for larger set people, or minimizing other.... prominent features.
A good compendium to have with!   P.s. for five star more categories and images
Simple design ... I like having sketches of models instead of actual photos... it makes you look at the pose and not the model or lighting.
Great for the aspiring professional or everyday photographer.
Puede tener mas!!! Pero es buena!!!
The poses are well explained
I really like this app. I wish they had a maternity or newborn section too.
Good app, great poses, like the way poses are devided. Also could use more...
I was waiting for years for this COMPLETE All-In-One application. Keep up good working!
This is great for an avid amateur photographer such as myself trying to get into portrait photography
The stick figure approach is brilliant
Great idea, nicely implemented but at 8mb it's way too big for phone install on anything but the most modern phones. On mine, it's second only to bloated Flash.  Please enable SD card installation.
Very nice, good features. Like others, could use more pooses, also, if it could be installled on SD card, good too
This app is great and the illustrations are really nice. The only problem, as stated by others, it needs more poses.
Please do something. Thanks
So far the app functions perfectly. Love the pic examples as they are easy to understand. Needs more poses though.
Liked it so far.. Would like to see more poses tho..

4 stars for showing some basics of photography..etc.etc...not just poses... cannot give 5 stars as we have not too many poses in there..and most of them are pretty common..every budding photographer would know.  Like to see more exciting and new poses...good app keep adding more..
Thank you so much for this app! Some descriptions need finishing but the pics are what's valuable.
